Source_name.0: STEREOB>SolarTerrestrial Relations Observatory Behind of the Sun-Earth Line

Descriptor.0: IMPACT>In-situ Measurements of Particles and CME Transients

TEXT.0: This file contains Beacon data from the IMPACT experiment on the STEREO Behind spacecraft.

TEXT.1: Note: The onboard SWEA calculation of moments and PADs are compromised by a charging effect at low energies. STE-U is not providing any science data as the instrument is blinded by sunlight and thus these variables are not accessible via CDAWeb

CAVEAT.0: IMPACT Beacon data is not science quality data.  Instead users should use IMPACT Level 1 data when it becomes available. These Beacon data are provided to allow event detection and preliminary analysis while the Level 1 data are processed, which sometimes takes a few months.

LINK_TEXT.0: Experiment and Data descriptions for STEREO/IMPACT
